# Cushion Cut Diamond Necklace: Prices, Styles & What to Know

Cushion cut diamond necklaces start at [$700 for a lab-grown 1/4 ct solitaire pendant in 14K white gold](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/necklaces/cushion-cut-lab-grown-diamond-solitaire-pendant-in-14k-white-gold-1-4-ct-tw-f-g-vs2-si1-item-251295?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational). Natural cushion pendants start at [$1,190 for 1/4 ct](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/necklaces/cushion-cut-diamond-solitaire-pendant-in-14k-white-gold-1-4-ct-tw-h-i-si1-si2-item-251293?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational). At 1 carat — the most popular pendant size — lab runs [$1,148](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/necklaces/cushion-cut-lab-grown-diamond-solitaire-pendant-in-14k-white-gold-1-ct-tw-f-g-vs2-si1-item-251302?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) and natural runs [$5,460](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/necklaces/cushion-cut-diamond-solitaire-pendant-in-14k-white-gold-1-ct-tw-h-i-si1-si2-item-251300?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational).

That gap tells you the story. Lab cushion pendants cost 79% less at 1ct with better grade specs. Most buyers choose lab. But there is one case where natural wins — and it has nothing to do with the stone looking different. This guide covers both.

