## The Colour Cut Advantage

This is why famous coloured diamond pendants are almost always cushion or radiant cut.

Round brilliant diamonds are cut to maximize white light. Every facet is positioned to bounce light back to your eye. That brightness is stunning.

But it also washes out body colour. A yellow round diamond shows less colour than a yellow cushion of the same grade — the white flashes compete with the warmth.

Cushion cuts have bigger facets. They let the body colour show through. A yellow cushion diamond looks more saturated than a yellow round at the same colour grade.

As a pendant, this effect is stronger. Your pendant moves and hangs from a chain, shifting as you walk. The cushion's large facets catch room light at constantly changing angles. Each slight tilt shows a different slice of the stone — warm one moment, a flash of white the next.

This is The Colour Cut Advantage. For the white lab cushion pendants in this guide (F-G colour), it's not the primary reason to buy. You're buying because the cushion looks beautiful — a different kind of beautiful than round.

But for anyone considering a yellow, pink, or cognac cushion diamond pendant, this is exactly why those pieces look the way they do. The colour concentrates in the stone and comes through clearly.

Even with a colourless cushion, the effect shows differently than a round pendant. White cushion pendants have more depth to look into. The bigger facets let you see the stone's interior.

It's a more contemplative sparkle — less "ball of light" and more "stone you look through." Some buyers strongly prefer it. Some prefer the high-flash brightness of round. But it's genuinely different, and knowing why helps you decide before buying.

