At 1 carat: natural is [$5,460](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/necklaces/cushion-cut-diamond-solitaire-pendant-in-14k-white-gold-1-ct-tw-h-i-si1-si2-item-251300?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational), lab is [$1,148](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/necklaces/cushion-cut-lab-grown-diamond-solitaire-pendant-in-14k-white-gold-1-ct-tw-f-g-vs2-si1-item-251302?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational). That is a $4,312 gap for lower grade specs (H-I vs F-G colour, SI1-SI2 vs VS2-SI1 clarity) in the natural stone.

Why does anyone buy natural? Provenance. The meaning of a mined diamond. The long-term value. For a pendant worn every day, these may not matter much. For a gift with sentimental weight — an anniversary, a milestone, something meant to be passed down — natural carries that story.

