- [Platinum — $5,550](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/necklaces/cushion-cut-diamond-solitaire-pendant-in-platinum-1-ct-tw-h-i-si1-si2-item-251301?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) (H-I/SI1-SI2, 14 reviews)

The lab version has better colour (F-G) and better clarity (VS2-SI1) for $4,312 less. SI1-SI2 clarity in a pendant is eye-clean at viewing distance — you won't see inclusions on a pendant worn at the collarbone. But the colour difference can show in direct light. F-G looks cooler and whiter. H-I has a faint warmth — barely visible in yellow gold, more noticeable in white gold settings.

For most buyers, the [lab 1ct at $1,148](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/necklaces/cushion-cut-lab-grown-diamond-solitaire-pendant-in-14k-white-gold-1-ct-tw-f-g-vs2-si1-item-251302?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) wins easily.

