## Cushion Cut Diamond Solitaire Necklace

The solitaire pendant is a single cushion diamond in a simple prong setting on a chain. No halo. No cluster. Just the stone.

This is the classic format for a cushion diamond necklace. The solitaire lets the cushion show what it is — the soft square silhouette, the large-facet fire, the warm romantic character. Nothing competes with the stone.

Full white gold lab cushion solitaire range:
- [$700 — 1/4 ct](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/necklaces/cushion-cut-lab-grown-diamond-solitaire-pendant-in-14k-white-gold-1-4-ct-tw-f-g-vs2-si1-item-251295?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) — entry level, delicate
- [$833 — 1/2 ct](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/necklaces/lab-grown-diamond-cushion-cut-solitaire-pendant-in-14k-white-gold-1-2-ct-tw-f-g-vs2-si1-item-202314?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) — visible, everyday
- [$959 — 3/4 ct](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/necklaces/lab-grown-diamond-cushion-cut-solitaire-pendant-in-14k-white-gold-3-4-ct-tw-f-g-vs2-si1-item-202313?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) — solid midpoint
- [$1,148 — 1 ct](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/necklaces/cushion-cut-lab-grown-diamond-solitaire-pendant-in-14k-white-gold-1-ct-tw-f-g-vs2-si1-item-251302?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) — sweet spot
- [$1,400 — 1.5 ct](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/necklaces/cushion-cut-lab-grown-diamond-solitaire-pendant-in-14k-white-gold-1-1-2-ct-tw-f-g-vs2-si1-item-251303?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) — notable presence
- [$1,785 — 2 ct](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/necklaces/cushion-cut-lab-grown-diamond-solitaire-pendant-in-14k-white-gold-2-ct-tw-f-g-vs2-si1-item-251304?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) — statement
- [$2,674 — 3 ct](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/necklaces/cushion-cut-lab-grown-diamond-solitaire-pendant-in-14k-white-gold-3-ct-tw-f-g-vs2-si1-item-251305?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) — fine jewelry presence

The cushion shape sits naturally in a four-prong solitaire setting. The prongs go at the four corners and hold the stone open. Light enters from all sides.

The stone tilts slightly as you move — and with a cushion's large facets, that movement catches light in a way a prong-set round doesn't. Each angle change shows a different flash. It's one of the reasons cushion pendants look so alive when worn rather than just sitting in a case.

