## Cushion Cut Diamond Bezel Necklace

A bezel pendant wraps the cushion diamond in a continuous metal border. No prongs. The metal runs around the full edge of the stone.

This gives a clean, modern look. Bezel settings are also more protective — no prongs to catch on clothing or bend over time. For a pendant worn every day, that protection is real.

The tradeoff: a bezel adds a metal rim around the stone's perimeter. It changes the aesthetic from delicate to architectural. The cushion diamond's soft corners inside a hard metal frame creates an interesting contrast — the cushion silhouette softened further by being contained in a clean geometric border.

For colour: a bezel setting can slightly warm up a diamond if the metal tone reflects into the stone's underside. Yellow gold bezel on an F-G colour lab cushion will add a small amount of warmth. White gold bezel stays neutral.

The cushion solitaire pendant range starting at [$700](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/necklaces/cushion-cut-lab-grown-diamond-solitaire-pendant-in-14k-white-gold-1-4-ct-tw-f-g-vs2-si1-item-251295?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) includes both prong and bezel setting options across different product listings. If you specifically want bezel, look for it in the setting description on the product page before purchasing.

