## Cushion Cut Diamond Necklace White Gold

White gold is the most popular metal for cushion diamond pendant necklaces. It keeps the diamond looking its whitest. It photographs cleanly — the metal blends near the stone so the diamond looks even larger in photos.

For F-G colour lab cushion pendants in white gold, the stone reads cold and bright. No warmth added by the metal. The combination of the cushion's romantic silhouette and white gold's crisp look creates a balance between character and elegance.

14K white gold is the standard for pendant settings. It's more durable than 18K and indistinguishable in daily wear. Rhodium plating keeps it looking silvery-white. For a pendant (which has less friction wear than a ring), the plating lasts longer.

