## Cushion Cut vs Round Diamond Necklace

The most common question before buying: cushion or round for a pendant?

Round brilliant is the safe choice. Every jeweler sells them. Everyone knows what they look like. The round pendant reads as a classic diamond necklace — clean, bright, unmistakably a diamond from across the room.

Cushion is the interesting choice. The soft square silhouette is different. It has a vintage romance that round doesn't carry. People notice it and ask about it.

**Sparkle character:**
Round pendants are bright and flashy. The cut is engineered for maximum white light return. You get a ball of sparkle that catches every light in the room. Cushion pendants have bigger, slower flashes — more fire (coloured light) and less "mirror ball" brightness. The sparkle is deeper and warmer. Neither is better. They're genuinely different aesthetics.

**Face-up size:**
Round brilliant cuts look slightly larger face-up than cushions at the same carat. A round 1ct measures about 6.5mm across. A cushion 1ct can measure anywhere from 5.5mm to 6.5mm depending on the cut style — modified brilliant cushions tend to look slightly smaller face-up. But the cushion has more depth, so the stone looks more three-dimensional when you look into it.

**Colour in the stone:**
Round pendants scatter colour into white flashes. Cushion pendants hold body colour. If you want the stone to look as white and bright as possible, round wins. If you want warmth, depth, or are considering a coloured diamond eventually, cushion shows it better.

**Who should choose round:**
You want the universally safe choice. You want maximum brightness from any angle. The person receiving it is more traditional in their jewelry taste.

**Who should choose cushion:**
You want something a little different. You love the vintage look. You want a stone that looks interesting at varying light angles. You're open to coloured diamonds down the road.

For the same carat and specs, round and cushion pendants are close in price. The [lab cushion 1ct at $1,148](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/necklaces/cushion-cut-lab-grown-diamond-solitaire-pendant-in-14k-white-gold-1-ct-tw-f-g-vs2-si1-item-251302?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) gives you a full carat with F-G/VS2-SI1. The choice between cuts is purely about which look you want to wear.

