## Frequently Asked Questions

### What is a cushion cut diamond necklace?
A cushion cut diamond necklace is a pendant necklace with a cushion-shaped diamond — square or slightly rectangular with soft, rounded corners. Common styles include solitaire (one stone in a prong or bezel setting), cluster (multiple stones in a cushion arrangement), and station (stones spaced along a chain). The cushion shape gives a softer, more romantic outline than a princess cut or the classic circle of a round brilliant.

### How much does a cushion cut diamond pendant necklace cost?
Lab-grown cushion solitaire pendants start at [$700 for 1/4 ct in 14K white gold](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/necklaces/cushion-cut-lab-grown-diamond-solitaire-pendant-in-14k-white-gold-1-4-ct-tw-f-g-vs2-si1-item-251295?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational). Natural cushion pendants start at [$1,190 for 1/4 ct](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/necklaces/cushion-cut-diamond-solitaire-pendant-in-14k-white-gold-1-4-ct-tw-h-i-si1-si2-item-251293?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational). At 1 carat — the most popular size — lab is [$1,148](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/necklaces/cushion-cut-lab-grown-diamond-solitaire-pendant-in-14k-white-gold-1-ct-tw-f-g-vs2-si1-item-251302?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) and natural is [$5,460](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/necklaces/cushion-cut-diamond-solitaire-pendant-in-14k-white-gold-1-ct-tw-h-i-si1-si2-item-251300?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational). All current certified market pricing includes 30% off for solitaire styles.

### Should I buy lab or natural for a cushion diamond necklace?
Lab for most buyers. The lab pendants come in F-G/VS2-SI1 — better specs than natural (H-I/SI1-SI2) at 79% less cost at 1ct. For a pendant that hangs at the collarbone and moves freely, the visual difference between lab and natural is zero to anyone looking at you. Natural makes sense if the necklace is a gift meant to be kept long-term, or if the mined origin matters personally.

### What carat size is best for a cushion diamond pendant necklace?
1 carat is the sweet spot for most buyers. At pendant distance (16-18 inches down from your face), 1 ct is clearly visible from arm's length. Small enough for everyday. Large enough to read as a real piece of jewelry. The [lab 1 ct at $1,148](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/necklaces/cushion-cut-lab-grown-diamond-solitaire-pendant-in-14k-white-gold-1-ct-tw-f-g-vs2-si1-item-251302?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) is the most popular option. If budget allows, the [2 ct at $1,785](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/necklaces/cushion-cut-lab-grown-diamond-solitaire-pendant-in-14k-white-gold-2-ct-tw-f-g-vs2-si1-item-251304?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) is only $637 more for double the stone.

### What is the Colour Cut Advantage for cushion diamond necklaces?
Cushion cuts have larger facets than round brilliants. Those big facets hold body colour instead of scattering it into white light. A yellow or cognac cushion pendant looks more colour-saturated than a round of the same grade. As a pendant that moves on a chain, the cushion's large facets catch ambient light at constantly changing angles — showing depth and warmth that a round pendant doesn't show in the same way.

### What chain length is best for a cushion diamond pendant?
18 inches is the most flattering for most cushion pendant sizes. The pendant sits just below the collarbone — visible and elegant. A 16-inch chain positions the pendant at the collarbone itself, giving a more delicate look. A 20-inch chain drops the pendant further down the chest — better for larger pendants (2ct and above) where you want more visual space around the stone.

### What metal is best for a cushion cut diamond pendant necklace?
White gold for a clean, modern look that keeps F-G colour stones looking their coldest white. Yellow gold for warmth — it adds a gentle glow to the stone's apparent colour and suits warm skin tones. Platinum for the most durable, hypoallergenic, and prestigious option at a small premium ($90 over white gold at 1ct). Natural pendants come in all three. Lab pendants come in white and yellow gold.

### What is a cushion cut diamond solitaire necklace?
A solitaire necklace has one cushion diamond in a simple prong or bezel setting — no surrounding stones, no cluster. It's the classic pendant format and the most popular style for cushion diamond necklaces. The solitaire lets the stone show its shape and sparkle without anything competing for attention. Lab cushion solitaire pendants start at [$700 for 1/4 ct](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/necklaces/cushion-cut-lab-grown-diamond-solitaire-pendant-in-14k-white-gold-1-4-ct-tw-f-g-vs2-si1-item-251295?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) in white gold.

### What is a cushion cut diamond halo necklace?
A halo necklace has a ring of small diamonds around the center cushion stone. The center looks larger and the total piece sparkles from more surface area. A similar option in the current certified lab lineup is the [Fancy Cluster Lab-Grown Diamond Necklace by James Allen at $1,260](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/necklaces/fancy-cluster-lab-grown-diamond-necklace-in-14k-white-gold-by-james-allen-item-311212?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) (50% off) — multiple lab stones in a cushion arrangement that gives similar visual impact to a halo design.

### What is a cushion cut diamond bezel necklace?
A bezel pendant wraps the cushion diamond in a continuous metal border — no prongs. The stone sits in a metal frame that runs around its perimeter. This gives a clean, geometric look and offers more protection than prongs. The cushion's soft corners inside a clean metal rim creates an interesting contrast between the stone's organic shape and the setting's sharp lines. Bezel cushion pendants look modern and architectural.

### How does a cushion cut diamond pendant look compared to a round pendant?
Round brilliant pendants sparkle more brightly — they maximize light return and look like a ball of white light. Cushion pendants have bigger, slower flashes with more visible fire (coloured light from dispersion). Round is the classic, universally safe choice. Cushion is a softer, more romantic look. For coloured diamonds, cushion shows the colour more intensely. For colourless diamonds, it comes down to which sparkle character you prefer.

### Are cushion cut diamond pendant necklaces good gifts?
Yes. A cushion diamond pendant is versatile — works for everyday and special occasions. The shape is softer than princess or round, which some people specifically prefer. The [lab 1 ct at $1,148](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/necklaces/cushion-cut-lab-grown-diamond-solitaire-pendant-in-14k-white-gold-1-ct-tw-f-g-vs2-si1-item-251302?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) is a strong gift at that budget. The [natural 1 ct at $5,460](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/necklaces/cushion-cut-diamond-solitaire-pendant-in-14k-white-gold-1-ct-tw-h-i-si1-si2-item-251300?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) is the right choice for a gift intended as a keepsake.

### How do I care for a cushion cut diamond pendant necklace?
Clean monthly with warm water, mild soap, and a soft brush. Rinse well and dry with a lint-free cloth. Store separately from other jewelry to prevent chain tangling and scratching. Check the bail (the loop connecting pendant to chain) and the prongs twice a year — the bail is the part most likely to wear through over time. Diamond itself doesn't scratch, but the gold setting does — avoid harsh chemicals and abrasive surfaces.

### Does a cushion cut diamond pendant look smaller than a round at the same carat?
It can, slightly. Round brilliant diamonds are cut to maximize face-up spread — a 1ct round is about 6.5mm across. Cushion cuts sacrifice some spread for depth. A 1ct cushion may measure 5.5–6.5mm depending on the specific cut style. The tradeoff is that the cushion has more visual depth — you look into the stone rather than at a flat surface of sparkle. Most buyers feel the cushion looks as large as a round of the same weight once they see both in person, because the depth gives it presence that measurements don't capture.

### What is the difference between a cushion cut and princess cut necklace?
Both are square-ish shaped diamonds, but they look very different as pendants. Princess cuts have sharp 90-degree corners. They look modern, geometric, and architectural. Cushion cuts have soft rounded corners — they look romantic, vintage-inspired, and organic. Sparkle character also differs: princess cuts produce a cross or X-shaped sparkle pattern, while cushion cuts produce big flowing flashes similar to round brilliants but warmer. For pendants, the soft corners of a cushion also mean fewer wear points — the corners of a princess-cut pendant setting can catch and wear down faster than a cushion's rounded edges.
